# Bee hives live in the enclosing project folder, not the repo. Only the
# testplans hive (consumed by the Docker harness) stays in-tree. If a future
# `tickets/<Other>/` directory appears inside the repo it should NOT be
# committed — the hive belongs outside.
tickets/*
!tickets/testplans/
!tickets/testplans/**

